    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Lincoln</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 267.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 229 of the 5th instant,
                        concerning your interview with Lord Salisbury with reference to the
                        resumption of diplomatic relations between Great Britain and Venezuela, has
                        been received.</p>
                <p>The substance of your dispatch has been communicated to the Venezuelan
                        minister at this capital and a copy thereof transmitted to our minister at
                        Caracas for his information.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
